nib.text:
One man was killed and and a second critically injured during a shooting in Payne-Phalen Friday night, officials said.

Police responded to multiple reports of a shooting in the 1200 block of Westminster Street just before 7:00 p.m.

Upon arrival, officers located a man with a gunshot wound.

Medics pronounced the victim deceased at the scene.

Shortly afterward, officers learned that a second victim was privately transported to an area hospital.

A spokesperson from the SPPD reported that he is in critical condition.

No arrests have been made. This investigation is ongoing.

Homicide detectives ask anyone with information to call (651) 266-5650.
